SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260325T193728Z
DTSTART:20260326T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Thursday\, March 26\, 2026\, 10:30am - 3:30pm\n\nTrained volunt
	eers will be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax return
	s.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nColumbia Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting Room\n\n
	Registration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Descripti
	on: This service is free and available to individuals only. The free servi
	ce is not available for business tax returns. To receive tax help\, bring 
	the following documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto identification\, Social S
	ecurity cards or Individual Taxpayer Identification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for
	 everyone listed on the tax return.\, Proof of income\, for example\, W2s 
	and 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Official documents on Social Se
	curity Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \\(if Social Security num
	ber is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to provide information about he
	alth care coverage for each person on the return.\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLas
	t year&'s tax return\, if available\, Bank account and routing numbers for
	 direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer print-outs of any of 
	these documents willbe accepted.\, Due to federal budget cuts the IRS is u
	nable to provide the Library with certain tax forms and instruction bookle
	ts.\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n\nwww.irs.gov .\, You may ma
	ke free black-and-white prints of the forms from Library computers:\n\nwww
	.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nAARP .\n\nEvent Logistics: Regi
	stration is not required but recommended. Register\n\nhere. \, AARP Tax He
	lp locations serve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025.\, For eli
	gibility details\, contact AARP at 888-227-7669.\n\nContact Us: If you hav
	e questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA A
	ccommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabilities 
	at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the
	 event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and open
	 to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-
	help/18162991/2026-03-26T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
