BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5jvDzKJJxN_jZUKr0zsK_
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260325T193728Z
DTSTART:20260326T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-26T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-26T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3CjXvtyUarldv6ROG_8gB
SUMMARY:Scott Gibson - Visual Symphony II
DTSTAMP:20260325T193728Z
DTSTART:20260326T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:In March\, Visual Symphony II Scott Gibson invites viewers into
	 a world where music and art collide. Each work is an exploration of the v
	ivid\, sensory experience of sound translating into vibrant\, emotional vi
	suals. As an artist with synesthesia each work expresses Scott’s personal 
	perception of what music looks like. Scott uses resin techniques that he h
	as pioneered and pushes the boundaries of this medium.\n\nhttps://seatoday
	.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symphony-ii/18280602/202
	6-03-26T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/scott-gibson-visual-symph
	ony-ii/18280602/2026-03-26T00
LOCATION:Gray Sky Gallery\, 320 First Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Mkne11xEPfBxd2E5GKgwH
SUMMARY:Denkyem Drop In and CoLab
DTSTAMP:20260325T193728Z
DTSTART:20260326T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Thursday\, March 26\, 2026\, 12:30 - 2:30pm\n\nJoin Denkyem sta
	ff and a business librarian to update your business plan with industry ins
	ights\, access market research\, or bounce ideas off the like-minded entre
	preneurs. Let&'s CoLab!\n\nLocation Link:\n\nBeacon Hill Branch\n\nRoom Lo
	cation: Lobby\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is required.\n\nDetai
	led Description: CoLab is a space for Collaboration\, Community and Cowork
	ing: a multifaceted approach to activate space for community\, specificall
	y Black Business owners to engage\, learn and network in meaningful ways.\
	, Thanks to our partner\n\nDenkyem Coop .\n\nEvent Logistics: Registration
	 required. Click\n\nhere\n\nto register.\, Light snacks and refreshments w
	illbe provided.\, This program was designed for Black business owners and 
	is free and open to all. The Library celebrates and reflects the voices\, 
	experiences and perspectives of Seattle's diverse communities in our space
	s\, collections and programs.\, Learn more about the Library's equity effo
	rts at\n\nwww.spl.org/Equity .\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about 
	this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We 
	can provide accommodations for people with disabilities at Library events.
	 Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request 
	accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and open to the public.\,\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/denkyem-drop-in-and-colab
	/17738949/2026-03-26T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/denkyem-drop-in-and-colab
	/17738949/2026-03-26T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jVLdjZ98MIJ_HarB8BPa4
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260325T193728Z
DTSTART:20260326T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Thursday\, March 26\, 2026\, 12:30 - 6:30pm\n\nTrained voluntee
	rs will be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.
	\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 5 - Mixing C
	hamber Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required
	.\n\nDetailed Description: This service is free and available to individua
	ls only. The free service is not available for business tax returns.\, To 
	receive tax help\, bring the following documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto 
	identification\, Social Security cards or Individual Taxpayer Identificati
	on Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyone listed on the tax return\, Proof of inc
	ome\, for example\, W2s and 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Officia
	l documents on Social Security Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \
	\(if Social Security number is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to prov
	ide information about health care coverage for each person on the return\,
	\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year&'s tax return\, if available\, Bank account 
	and routing numbers for direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or compute
	r print-outs of any of these documents will be accepted.\, Due to federal 
	budget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain tax form
	s and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n\nww
	w.irs.gov. \, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms from L
	ibrary computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nUnited 
	Way of King County .\n\nEvent Logistics: United Way Tax Help locations ser
	ve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025 \\(or less than $96\,000 f
	or non-single filers\\).\, For eligibility details\, contact United Way at
	 206-461-3700.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\n
	Ask Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide acco
	mmodations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\nconta
	ctLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\
	, All Library programs are free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seato
	day.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-03-26T00\n\nF
	rom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-03-26T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
